(firstQuint)Vitamin D Replacement in Statin-Induced Myopathy.

 Patients who have been unable to tolerate statin medications due to muscle pain will be randomly assigned to receive vitamin D or placebo for 6 weeks before reintroducing their statin medication.

 The investigators will judge whether vitamin D in the manner administered in the study reduces the myalgia with statins and allows patients to remain on these important medications.

